<p><b>Paolo Soleri</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1919-06-21"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="06-21"><a href="/wiki/June_21" title="June 21">June 21</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1919" title="1919">1919</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/Italian-American" title="Italian-American" class="mw-redirect">Italian-American</a> visionary architect with a life-long commitment to research and experimentation in design and <a href="/wiki/Town_planning" title="Town planning" class="mw-redirect">town planning</a>. He established <a href="/wiki/Arcosanti" title="Arcosanti">Arcosanti</a> and the educational <a href="/wiki/Cosanti" title="Cosanti">Cosanti</a> Foundation. Soleri is a distinguished lecturer in the College of Architecture at <a href="/wiki/Arizona_State_University" title="Arizona State University">Arizona State University</a> and a <a href="/wiki/National_Design_Award" title="National Design Award" class="mw-redirect">National Design Award</a> recipient in 2006.</p>
